@NODE INTRODUCTION "Introduction...."

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

This door is written during the fact that aRTcORE! decided to make my BBS
to their German Headquarter. To let Users request something, they gave me
AsciiOrder written by Duplo...well I don't like this door, coz' it's a
little bit to simple....and therefor I decided to write my own aSKII-request
door....it has some nice features, like:

 - is able to simulate EALL messages to all painters

 - Additional Comment (3 Lines) possible, to give further infos 'bout the
   request...

 - Hole design is freely configurable during external ANSI-Pictures

 - Every Painter gets his own Datafile, reg. Users got l8er an Auto-Answer
   Mode, allowing aSKII-rEQUEST to automatically delete uploaded requests.

 - Creates a nice Bulletin about all Requests.

...etc. etc. etc...:) If you need such a program, look in the @{"Installation" LINK INSTALLATION}
chapter on how to install it...
@ENDNODE

@NODE INSTALLATION "How to install it to your BBS-System"

@{u}Installation@{uu}

This door runs under Fame and Amiex BBS-Systems, but was mainly written for
usage on Amiex, therefor special functions available under FAME aren't
supported!

The easiest way for installing is the Usage of the Installer-Script found
in this archive. This will install aSKII-rEQUEST and all needed files to
your system. If you want to install it by hand read now :

@{b}Installation to Amiex@{ub}

1. Copy aSKII-rEQUEST + aSKII-rEQUEST.info to your Doors: directory, I
   recommend to create an own drawer for this Program, as it creates Data-
   Files in the Program-Directory!

2. Copy the supplied 'ASCII.INFO' to your BBS:COMMANDS/BBSCMD/ drawer and
   adjust the path to the drawer you have put in aSKII-rEQUEST.

3. Now edit the ToolTypes. For more Informations take a look to chapter
   @{"ToolTypes" LINK TOOLTYPES}.

4. That's it..:)


@{b}Installation to FAME@{ub}

1. Copy aSKII-rEQUEST + aSKII-rEQUEST.info to your FAME:Doors directory, I
   recommend to create an own drawer for this Program, as it creates Data-
   Files in the Program-Directory!

2. Start the SystemEditor, go into the Doors-Menu and load in the supplied
   ANSI Command (aSKII-rEQUEST/FAME/SETTINGS/DOORS/BBSMCMD/ANSI). Adjust
   the Path to the Drawer where aSKII-reQUEST could be found.

3. Now edit the ToolTypes. For more Informations take a look to chapter
   @{"ToolTypes" LINK TOOLTYPES}.

4. That's it..:)
@ENDNODE

@NODE TOOLTYPES "Tooltype-Informations for aSKII-rEQUEST"

@{u}ToolTypes@{uu}

aSKII-rEQUEST needs some Tooltypes to work correctly. Here's a list :

SLOT.(x)=<SLOTNR.>    -> Here you define the painters available on your BBS.
                         You have to define here the Slot-Numbers to allow
                         aSKII-rEQUEST to write to the correct persons.
                         You need at least ONE painter to let the prg working.
                         Of course you could have as many painters as you like.

                         @{b}Example:@{ub}

                                 SLOT.1=17
                                 SLOT.2=82
                                 SLOT.3=444


SHOW_AS.(x)=<STRING>  -> Here you could define alternate Names for the
                         painters. If you don't define this Tooltype, the
                         current Username is used. If you defined it, the
                         Name you entered here will be displayed when showing
                         the artists instead of the Painter's real Username.

                         @{b}Example:@{ub}

                               SHOWN_AS.1=2fAST/aRTCORE
                               SHOWN_AS.2=sTYLeZ/^nEON^aRTCORE
                               SHOWN_AS.3=(-rAPiD-)/sCOOPeX^aRTCORE


OUTPUT_BULL=<PATH>    -> Here you could enter an alternate Path for creating
                         the Output-Bulletin containing the requests. If this
                         Tooltype isn't present, aSKII-rEQUEST uses his own
                         Path-Location as path, and creates in it a Bull called
                         ORDER.TXT. If you wish to create it in another path,
                         you *MUST* enter here a complete path including the
                         filename, otherwise aSKII-rEQUEST won't create the
                         BULL!

                         @{b}Example:@{ub}

                         You don't defined this Tooltype. aSKII-rEQUEST is
                         located in DOORS:ASKII-REQUEST/, then the Bull will
                         be created in 'DOORS:ASKII-REQUEST/ORDER.TXT' .

Currently no more Tooltypes available, but for registered Users will be a
major update in the next month...so get registered!
@ENDNODE

@NODE HOW2USE "How to use this Program"

@{u}How it works@{uu}

To allow Sysops to design this Door to their own needings, I have decided to
read in all screens from HD...so if you want to change the Style of this 
Door, simply edit the following files found in the drawer of aSKII-rEQUEST:

        ASKII-MAIN.TXT     --> ANSI for MainMenu
        ASKII-ENTER.TXT    --> ANSI for Menu ENTER REQUESTS
        ASKII-LIST.TXT     --> ANSI for Menu SHOW ARTISTS
        ASKII-DELETE.TXT   --> ANSI for Menu DELETE REQUESTS

Included in this archive are the Ansis painted by sTYLeZ of da famous 
aRT-cORE! posse...i think everyone will love them..:) You could of course
alternately use this door without any ANSI-Pictures, but who wants this..:)

@{u}Main-Usage of aSKII-rEQUEST@{uu}

When starting aSKII-rEQUEST, you have the following choices :

                    @{" 1 " LINK HELP_1} ->  rEQUEST aN aSCII
                    @{" 2 " LINK HELP_2} ->  deLETE rEQUESTS
                    @{" 3 " LINK HELP_3} ->  vIEW rEQUESTS
                    @{" 4 " LINK HELP_4} ->  sHOW aRTISTS
                    @{" 5 " LINK HELP_5} ->  qUIT pROGRAM

Click on number (1-5) you want more informations about...

The Output-Bulletin will be created each time the user exits the program.
So if you want to see the Bull, simply start and exit immediatly the door ;)
@ENDNODE

@NODE HELP_1 "Help on 'REQUEST AN ASCII'"

@{u}REQUEST AN ASCII@{uu}

Here you request ansis..:) when selected, you were first prompted if you want
to write a Pseudo-EALL Message to all available painters. If you answer here
No, you could choose the Painter you wish to request something. By pressing
only Enter, you got back to the main menu. 
After choosing the Painter, you were now asked about the Type of logo you 
want to request. So you could enter here i.e. DMS-Banner, BBSTitle, etc... 
so the painter sees which type he should paint for you...:) Again only 
pressing Enter brings yar back to the main prompt...
Now you were asked for the Name on the Banner, here you should enter now the
Name you want to have painted...i.e. SieGeL etc..
At least, you could enter an additional comment to the painter(s) containing 
max. 3 lines with 78 chars each line. Only pressing enter exits the comment-
editor. Of course you could use this Comment-Editor as a real Line-Editor 
with CRSR-Left/Right support, DEL/BACKSPACe etc...

After all parameters are entered, aSKII-rEQUEST displays the complete
message to you and asks you if you really want to save this Message. Select
No to abort saving...if you have selected to write to ALL Painters, aSKII-
rEQUEST will now write a couple number of messages, depending on how many
painters are available. After successful saving, you will kicked back to
main menu.
@ENDNODE

@NODE HELP_2 "Help on 'DELETE REQUESTS'"

@{u}DELETE REQUESTS@{uu}

This Menu-Entry is only accessable for the Sysop and the Painters defined
in the aSKII-rEQUEST.info. Here you could delete old requests. For registered
Users a new tool will be written, which deletes requests automatically. In
this FreeVersion all painters have to delete their Requests for themself.
@ENDNODE

@NODE HELP_3 "Help on 'VIEW REQUESTS'"

@{u}VIEW REQUESTS@{uu}

With this point you could take a look to all available requests. When 
selecting this point, you where asked if you want to view the Requests from
ALL painters or from a single Painter. Depending on your choice you see the
requests.
@ENDNODE

@NODE HELP_4 "Help on 'SHOW ARTISTS'"

@{u}SHOW ARTISTS@{uu}

This point allows you to see which painters are available on this BBS. I 
think nothing more has to say about this point I think.......
@ENDNODE

@NODE HELP_5 "Help on 'QUIT PROGRAM'"

@{u}QUIT PROGRAM@{uu}

This exits aSKII-rEQUEST.
@ENDNODE

